- cut off the four upper fingers of the glove in latex so that the thumb remains intact;
- cut a piece of 30cm. silicone tube (see FASE 1);
- take the recently cut glove and insert it into the larger beaker of 250ml. using a piece of paper tape to ensure that it is sealed. Subsequently insert the silicone tube into the glove and secure it with a plastic strap (see FASE 2); 
- insert the other free end of the silicone tube into the U-shaped drying tube. Also in this case fix everything with a piece of paper tape (see FASE 3);
- position the pliers and the plastic base so that you can support the smaller beaker of 100ml. in one of the two pliers, then place it inside the U-shaped drying tube and close its free end with the rubber stopper (see FASE 4);
- move back to the larger beaker of 250ml. and cut off the thumb from the tip. Use the pliers to hold the U-shaped drying tube in place and secure it with a piece of paper tape (see FASE 5);
- fill the beaker of 250ml. with a water-alcohol mixture (see FASE 6);
- place the beaker of 250ml. on the tripod stand (see FASE 7);
- place the thermometer in the beaker of 250ml. (see FASE 8);
- start the distillation process by turning on the Bunsen burner (see FASE 9);
- observe the temperature of the water-alcohol mixture during the distillation process (see FASE 10);
- when the temperature of the water-alcohol mixture reaches 65°C, stop the distillation process (see FASE 11);
- remove the U-shaped drying tube from the beaker of 250ml. (see FASE 12);
- fill the beaker of 100ml. with distilled water (see FASE 13);
- place the beaker of 100ml. on the tripod stand (see FASE 14);
- place the U-shaped drying tube in the beaker of 100ml. (see FASE 15);
- start the distillation process by turning on the Bunsen burner (see FASE 16);
- observe the temperature of the distilled water during the distillation process (see FASE 17);
